# Udemy Course Auto-Complete 🚀

Script to automatically mark all lessons of a Udemy course as completed.

> ⚠️ **Use responsibly**: This script is useful for courses you have already watched or when Udemy fails to properly record your progress.

## 📖 Why I created this script

Back in 2024, I completed a few courses on Udemy and, after finishing all the lessons, moved on to other projects. Months later, when I logged back into the platform, I realized that **none of the courses were marked as completed** and several individual lessons hadn't been registered as watched either.

Since I had already dedicated hours to the content and didn't want to redo the entire process manually (clicking hundreds of checkboxes one by one), I developed this script to automate marking what I had already legitimately studied.

If you're in the same situation — whether due to a Udemy bug, watching lessons offline, or migrating accounts — this script will save you **hours of repetitive clicking**.

## 🎯 Features

- ✅ Automatically expands all course sections
- ✅ Marks all pending lessons as completed
- ✅ Two versions available:
  - **Fast**: Marks all items in seconds (may cause logout)
  - **Safe**: 1-second interval between clicks (recommended)

## 📥 How to Use

### Method 1: Browser Console (Recommended)

1. Go to your course page on Udemy
2. Scroll to the bottom of the page (to load all content)
3. Open the Developer Console:
   - **Windows/Linux**: `Ctrl + Shift + J` or `F12`
   - **Mac**: `Cmd + Option + J`
4. Paste the code from your chosen version and press `Enter`

### Method 2: Bookmarklet (Coming soon)

Create a bookmark with the code to run it with a single click.

## 📊 Version Comparison

| Version | Interval | Speed | Logout Risk | When to Use |
|---------|----------|-------|-------------|-------------|
| **fast-version.js** | 150ms | ~15 items/sec | High | Small courses (< 30 lessons) |
| **safe-version.js** | 1000ms | 1 item/sec | Low | Large courses or if you've been logged out before |

## 🔧 Troubleshooting

### ❌ "Found 0 items to mark"

**Cause**: Sections not expanded or content not loaded.

**Solution**: 
1. Manually scroll to the bottom of the page
2. Click to manually expand all sections
3. Run the script again

### ❌ I was logged out during execution

**Cause**: Too many requests in a short time.

**Solution**: Use `safe-version.js` with the 1000ms interval.

### ❌ Red errors in the console (`ERR_BLOCKED_BY_CLIENT`)

**Cause**: Your AdBlock is blocking Udemy's telemetry.

**Impact**: **None** on the script's functionality. Ignore these errors.

